article.description: J.C. Show scored 17 points and Binghamton rolled to 85-64 win over Delaware State on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Binghamton rolls to 85-64 win over Delaware State
article.linkText: Binghamton rolls to 85-64 win over Delaware State
article.story: DOVER, Del. -- J.C. Show scored 17 points and Binghamton rolled to 85-64 win over Delaware State on Wednesday night. Show was 6 of 10 from the field including five 3-pointers for the Bearcats (4-4). Thomas Bruce and Fard Muhammad added 14 points apiece and Everson Davis chipped in 11. Bruce led the team with 10 rebounds, earning his fourth double-double this season. The Bearcats averaged 58.5 percent shooting from the field, 83 percent from the line and 52 percent (13 of 25) from 3-point range. Binghamton jumped to a 25-9 start capped by a Muhammad 3-pointer with 11:25 to go in the half and led all the way, building to a 46-29 advantage by halftime. The Bearcats led by double figures throughout the second half, stretching their lead to 21 points, 73-52, on a Bobby Ahearn 3 with 8:53 left. Simon Okolue scored 15 points for the Hornets (2-6) who are 0-6 against Division I teams this season.
